    <p>
      My name is Carlos. I started <strong>programming back in school with Pascal</strong>, 
      where I got really frustrated because I couldn't code the classic "Snake" game. 
      Years later, in college, I tried Pascal again and once more failed to make that snake move. 
      It wasn’t until I discovered <strong>Java and Python</strong> that the world started to 
      look much brighter.
    </p>

    <p>
      Today, I work as an AI Backend Engineer, focused on <strong>designing, developing, 
      and maintaining backend services and AI-powered solutions</strong> for web platforms. 
      I also keep a strong <strong>DevOps</strong> mindset, working on CI/CD processes, 
      software architecture, quality, and testing. I specialize in backend development with 
      <strong>Python, Flask, FastAPI, Gunicorn, and Docker</strong>.
    </p>

    <p>
      Outside of programming, I'm passionate about <strong>CrossFit</strong> and sports in 
      general. I'm a huge fan of <strong>Rafa Nadal</strong> and <strong>Real Madrid</strong>.
    </p>
  </div>

